cloud computing models
  
  1 - infrastructure as a Service (Iaas)
  2 - Software as a Service (SaaS)
  2 - Platfom as a Service (PaaS)

Aws operate the 3 types.
 
1 - infrastructure as a Service (Iaas)
  
  Building Blocks
    Fundamental building blocks that can be rented 

  ex: 
      EC2.

      Web Hosting Blocks
        Monthly susbcrip. to have a hosting company server your website

2 - Software as a Service (SaaS)
  
  Complete Application
    Using a complete a application, on demand, that someone offers to users.

    Ex: 

      Sage Maker

      Email Provider
        Your personal email that you access though a web browser is SaaS.
  
3 - Platfom as a Service  (PaaS)

  Used by Developers
    Develop software using web-based tools without worrying the underlying infrastructure.

  Ex:
    CloudNine

    Storefront WebSite
      Tools provided to build a storefront application that runs on another company's server.

================================================================================================== 

Cloud Deployment Models

1 - Private Cloud (on-premises)

    Key Takeaways:
      Exist in your internal data center 
      Doesn't offer the advantages of cloud computing
      Increase level of security

2 - Public Cloud (AWS)

    Key Takeaways:
      U aren't responsible for the physical hardware
      Provides all the advantages of cloud computing

3 - Hybrid Cloud (AWS)
    
    end: Put the Private Data on the Private Cloud and Application on the Public Cloud.
